content: One of the greatest games I've ever played. Atmospheric, tense and even emotionally intense, TWOM offers an experience, not just a game. An astonishingly detailed and intense game with beautiful presentation and haunting music

The only reason why I didn't really like it is because as amazing as the 
game is with it's stories and soundtrack, along with great crafting, it's 
the 15$ price tag that kills it for me, just cut it down to 7-10 bucks and 
that will be remedied, but it made made me have buyers remorse for a while 
just because it was this or XCOM for awhile and I have had way more more 
fun with XCOM. No doubt, amazing game, it's just way too pricey. At least I 
would include The Little One's DLC just so that less people feel ripped 
off. And I hope that these changes can happen because it's so nice to see 
smaller game developers make such great games (unlike a certain 2 triple A 
companies) and I hate to see a game get ripped apart by so many, as while 
they do have a valid point with the price tag everything else is so well 
made, I love the steep difficulty at the beginning, it really can help you 
realize what type of game this is but not being as gut punchingly difficult 
as XCOM in the beginning, and I like how when the story progresses we learn 
more about our survivors. It makes the game that much more enjoyable. In 
conclusion, don't buy it for the full 15$, wait for a sale or if they cut 
down the price, I guarantee you that for 5 bucks or even 7 for a sale you 
will not be disappointed if you're into these types of games, but at least 
include TLO DLC and I can understand a little bit more the 15$ price tag.

content:
I wanted to write a much larger review but Google wouldn't allow the two 
pages of in-depth review i had... This game keeps resetting after i leave 
the app, which also resets the day for each gameplay, so all events and 
things built get reset, please fix this. Gameplay is tight and very 
crafting/strategy/multitasking oriented, but it's also very intense to the 
degree were you will stop caring about your characters. Would be nice if 
there was a tutorial + easier way of seeing updates to your inventory when 
you acquire new items and materials. Every day /play through feels like a 
constant punch to the gut, no matter what choice you choose. I know this is 
a survival game in war times, but i wish at times this game would be 
easier. I'm actually glad i bought this game at sale price for $4.00, the 
full price for this mobile port in my mind is not with it... But Either 
way, I'll be playing this game for a while, trying to get better and better 
for sure.

Feels like early access.  First of all, stop saying this is "realistic". One, the survival meters are better than most, but still not realistic. Two, characters being sad over their own killing, and stealing is actually unrealistic. Unless you've lived it your opinion doesn't count.  It's a good game. Looks nice. Great atmosphere. Compelling stories. Intense stealth. My first problem is with the balance. It's pretty easy if you don't help anyone who comes to the door, but drastically harder if you do. Also, choosing combat over stealth is almost always a death sentence. My huge problem is that halfway through my third run, after two complete ones, the lag during scavenging game breaking. I am unable to scavenge dangerous areas. Sometimes it's so lagged I can't move the screen back to the exits once they're out of sight. If the lag issue was fixed, I could easily forgive all else, and give it five stars. It's such a shamex and disappointment. I was really loving this game.

Edit: so I went back to the hotel with a crowbar to free what I thought was a captive. He said who are you and started running around the place screaming help. Dunno what was up with him. Everything from the gameplay, strategy to going out hunting for resources; dodging bullet & bombs.. This game is all about survival & helping others survive and creating a small community in a war zone. You can decide if you accept people who want to join, and if you let them in, you give them jobs and objectives. Every single person is important. Also you craft & create many things! You build up you're arsenal and storage for food. Build radios & other items. Make the community strive and survive the war..  So much more to it but i can't fit everything in this review. So if you're like me, not usually into these types of games.. I really urge you to get this one! It's absolutely amazing! So much to do, so much fun. And sometimes scary! And damn so it make your heart race! Love it! 5/5

Easily one of the greatest games in the play store. Here are my thoughts after beating the game: -Characters that you come to like and want to keep alive.  -Moral decisions that can lead to different endings for the characters.  -Not a fun (or particularly easy) game for the faint of heart, as it certainly has some heartwrenching moments, but worth every penny for both the OG game and the little ones DLC.  - A very long game with various degrees of difficulty (some characters are VERY difficult to work with due to lack of storage space, emotional stability or picking fights with other house members). I believe there are 12 different scenarios ranging from 30 to 50ish days with different combinations of characters.  -Definitely a lot of thought put into various senerios and how they impact your little band. Even includes crime outbreaks, changing weather, and food shortages. -Graphics are pretty good, all things considering.The last patch fixed all the bugs I'd had. Will be purchasing the PC version in the future! Great game!

This game is so great the second time around. Why the second time? Because you'll get your ass handed to you the first time. Incredible game that really makes you  strategise and think three days ahead, and improvise when your plan falls apart and you think," What about after the next three days." The game stylizes its self in a way that does everything BUT glorify wartime. By the end, you'll be proud of the strategy you've exhibited in taking down bandit settlements, yet disgusted with yourself for your other decisions. Firefights in this game can be almost as adrenaline inducing as a Dark Souls boss fight and you'll never feel worse in a game than when you accidentally kill someone who was just trying to give up. Great job, worth every penny. (Edit)- This has me pissed off though. Every time I load up the game it crashes. I hit continue and it restarts the title screen load-up. I wait about fifteen minutes each time I attempt to play the game. Please respond or update to fix stability.

Say you go somewhere, kill an innocent civilian because *that's what other games have conditioned you to do, right?* then your character gets sad, and that can make other characters sad. The game is rather difficult and its mechanics only add to the frustration. The three characters and their low tolerance thresholds, are far from survivalists; constantly hungry, constantly tired and easily wounded. It takes more resources than can be acquired to tend to their needs whilst at the same time having to create the various workstations required to build weapons and furniture, prepare meds and food etc. Out of smokes?? In times of war one would likely kick the habit, not these survivors, they get depressed and end up hanging themselves! This War of Mine is full of little nuances that inhibit any real enjoyment. If it was half the price I might say give it a go, but even then I'd advise that you think carefully before opening your wallet. There are plenty of comparable games that are free to play and far more enjoyable.

content: Pretty disappointed with this game.  Boring gameplay, grueling difficulty and HIGH retail sticker on this game leaves me regretting my purchase.  Suggested because I like strategy games and RPGs; was told that gameplay would be similar to Fallout Shelter.  Thought game would be randomized, but gameplay is pretty linear in that you have scenarios instead of just freeplay.  Unlock scenarios as you play, but ZERO replayabilty and every scenario plays out the same way (same home building, same random rubble, same etc...).  Semi-interesting realtime mechanics, but isn't suited by tablet (in my opinion).  Building elements placed too close together and fat-fingers will accidentally cancel orders.  There is a top-down post-apocalyptic survival game in the appstore that plays very similar, but it's open-story and is FREE.  Only redeeming element of this game is that profits are spent on a good charity, so I don't really feel like I've been too heavily gypped.

content: Fantastic refresh, it deviates from the military perspective, and goes into the struggles of civilians who were trapped in the war. Hold on to moral righteousness and struggle to get by, or accept the circumstances and commit a few crimes to help your people survive longer? On day 44 I realised I could tune the radio hahahahha!

Game of survival. While not a cheery game but brings to life aspects of struggling to live through the day. The graphics, sound all lend to the game experience.
Just a great game. Never have I had so much fun trying to get a group of civilians just to survive one more night.
